## Cross-Academy Fixtures

Monthly cross-academy meets include all three match types:

| Round | Type | Pairing Rule |
|------|------|--------------|
| Round 1 | Competitive | Swiss-style: pair closest-rated players across academies within each tier |
| Round 2 | Competitive | Swiss progression: pair based on Round 1 results |
| Round 3 | Stretch | Pair top half of each lower tier against bottom half of the upper tier across academies |

This gives each player 2 competitive cross-academy matches and 1 stretch cross-academy match per meet.

Cross-academy stretch matches carry the highest \(K_{\text{shared}}\) in the system:

$$
K_{\text{shared}}
$$

Components:

$$
W_{\text{match}} = 1.0 \quad (\text{league})
$$

$$
W_{\text{academy}} = 1.2 \quad (\text{cross-academy})
$$

Combined multiplier:

$$
W_{\text{effective}} =
W_{\text{match}} \times W_{\text{academy}} = 1.2
$$

Plus the natural Elo asymmetry of a stretch match.

These are the most impactful matches a player can play — a stretch win in a cross-academy meet is the single fastest way to gain rating.

