## Weekly and Season Totals

### Weekly (5 training days, 3 rated matches per session)

| Match Type | Per Day | Per Week |
|------------|----------|-----------|
| Competitive | 2 | 10 |
| Stretch / Anchor | 1 | 5 |
| **Total** | **3** | **15** |

---

### Season (16 weeks)

| Match Type | Within-Academy | Cross-Academy (4 meets × 3 matches) | Season Total |
|------------|----------------|--------------------------------------|--------------|
| Competitive | 160 | 8 | **168** |
| Stretch / Anchor | 80 | 4 | **84** |
| **Total** | **240** | **12** | **252** |

At 252 matches per season, a player completes their provisional period (15 matches) in the **first week**. They reach K_base = 32 (30 total matches) by **week 2**, and K_base = 20 (100 total matches) by **week 7**. Rating convergence happens fast.

---

## Comparison to Weekly Model

| Metric | Old (weekly) model | New (daily session) model |
|--------|-------------------|---------------------------|
| Matches per week | 4 | 15 |
| Matches per season | 76 | 252 |
| Provisional exit | Week 4 | Week 1 |
| K_base=32 reached | Week 8 | Week 2 |
| K_base=20 reached | Not in season | Week 7 |

The daily model produces 3× more matches, which means faster convergence, richer data, and more meaningful analytics.

