## Stretch Match Progression Tracking

The coaching analytics layer should track stretch match outcomes to measure developmental progress:

| Metric | What It Shows |
|--------|----------------|
| **Stretch win rate** | % of stretch matches won (across all stretch gaps). Rising trend indicates the player is outgrowing their tier |
| **Stretch win rate by gap** | Win rate at 100, 150, 200, 250 point gaps. Identifies the sweet spot where the player is competitive but challenged |
| **Stretch score quality** | Average S value in stretch losses (e.g., average 0.15 in losses means they’re losing close). Improving even without winning |
| **Promotion signal** | If stretch win rate against the next tier exceeds 40% for 4+ consecutive weeks, the player is likely ready for tier promotion |

This data is available through the coaching analytics dashboard and is not part of the rating system itself.

