## Example: Day 3 of Provisional Phase (Academy Y — New Launch)

Academy Y just launched. 16 players, all rated 1000. 4 tables. Best-of-3.

**Phase detection**: spread = 0 → **Phase A (discovery round-robin)**

---

### Day 1 (all at 1000)

Round-robin circle method, 3 rounds of 4 matches each:

```
Round 1: (1v16) (2v15) (3v14) (4v13) — on tables 1–4
Round 2: (5v12) (6v11) (7v10) (8v9) — on tables 1–4
Round 3: (1v15) (16v14) (2v13) (3v12) — on tables 1–4
```

After Day 1: 12 matches played. Rating spread: ~60 points (highest ~1030, lowest ~970).

---

### Day 3 (spread reached ~150 points)

**Phase detection**: spread = 150 → **Phase B (split round-robin)**

Players sorted by rating after 9 matches each:

- **Upper half** (8 players, ratings 1040–1120):
  - Round-robin within upper half for Rounds 1 and 3

- **Lower half** (8 players, ratings 880–960):
  - Round-robin within lower half for Rounds 1 and 3

- **Cross-half for Round 2**:
  - Top of lower half faces bottom of upper half (stretch/anchor)

---

### Day 7 (spread reached ~300 points)

**Phase detection**: spread = 300 → **Phase C (standard algorithm)**

Players now span Beginner through Advanced. Full competitive/stretch/anchor fixture generation activates. Most players have completed 15+ matches and exited provisional.

The system bootstrapped itself in one week with zero external input.

---

## Summary

| Design Choice | Decision | Rationale |
|--------------|----------|-----------|
| Session model | Daily 2–3 hour blocks, 3 rated matches per session | Matches real academy training schedules |
| Match mix | 50% competitive, 25% stretch, 25% anchor per session | Balances rating accuracy with developmental growth |
| Session algorithm | C-S-C-S (even tiers) or C-C-S-C (any odd tier) — auto-selected per session | C-S-C-S maximises variety; C-C-S-C completes 3-player tier round-robins |
| Provisional bootstrapping | 3-phase auto-transition (Discovery → Split → Standard) | Self-starting, no coach seeding needed |
| Bootstrap duration | ~5–10 training days to reach standard fixtures | K=60 + round-robin produces rapid separation |
| Phase detection | Based on rating spread of present players | Simple, automatic, runs daily |

---

| Stretch gap | 100–250 points | Win rate of 19–36% — challenging but achievable |
| Stretch rating treatment | Standard Elo, no special weights | Math already produces favorable 3:1+ risk/reward |
| Cross-academy stretch | 1 per monthly meet | Highest-impact match type in the system |
| Season total | ~252 matches (15/week × 16 weeks + cross-academy) | Fast convergence, exits provisional in week 1 |
